FBIS4-43094 "drweu113_p_94010" FBIS-WEU-94-113 Daily Report 11 Jun 1994 GREECE Explosions Rock Athens, Group Claims Responsibility Explosions Rock Athens, Group Claims Responsibility NC1106063094 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in Greek 0400 GMT 11 Jun 94 NC1106063094 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network Greek BFN [Text] There was a barrage of explosions last night in the center of Athens. Specifically, within 15 minutes at around midnight homemade explosive devices went off in a school bus from the Kostas Yitonas educational institute at the intersection of Skiros and Evelpidhes Streets in Kipseli [Athens suburb], at a refreshment shop on Andrianos Street in Plaka [Athens district], and outside the Thivai textile mill on Kapnitareas Street. A very strong explosion also took place at 0230 today at the intersection of Vasilissis Sofias and (Iridhanos) Streets, destroying a small, white truck with the registration No. YZ8660. The Antiauthority Battle [Andiexousiastiki Pali] organization made a telephone call to a private radio station claiming responsibility only for the first explosion.
